overview:
Redmi Note 13 Pro mobile comes with a 6.67-inch touchscreen display offering a resolution of 1080x2400 pixels and an aspect ratio of 20:9.Redmi Note 13 Pro comes with 16GB of RAM. The Redmi Note 13 Pro runs Android 12 and is powered by a 5100mAh non-removable battery. The Redmi Note 13 Pro supports 67W Turbo Charge fast charging.
As far as the cameras are concerned, the Redmi Note 13 Pro on the rear packs a triple camera setup featuring a 200-megapixel primary camera; an 8-megapixel camera, and a 2-megapixel camera. It has a single front camera setup for selfies, featuring a 16-megapixel sensor.
The Redmi Note 13 Pro runs MIUI 13 is based on Android 12 and packs 512GB of inbuilt storage. The Redmi Note 13 Pro is a dual-SIM (GSM) mobile that accepts Nano-SIMmobile. The Redmi Note 13 Pro measures 161.15 x 74.24 x 7.98mm (height x width x thickness) and weighs 187.00 grams. It was launched in Black, Blue, Silver, and White colour.
Connectivity options on the Redmi Note 13 Pro include Wi-Fi, GPS, Bluetooth v5.20, NFC, USB Type-C, 3G, and 4G (with support for Band 40 used by some LTE networks in India). Sensors on the phone include an accelerometer, ambient light sensor, proximity sensor, and fingerprint sensor.
